Safety-ScoreExpl: The Safety Score is computed by Beefyâ€™s developers when assessing a vault. No score can capture risk levels perfectly, but Beefy finds it a useful gauge in making decisions. The Safety Score ranks a vault from 0 to 10, worst to best.
Safety-HigherSafer: The Safety Score breaks down the safety of the underlying vault asset into several key factors. It aims to draw your attention to the risks to consider before investing, and to inform you about technical details that you may not be able to evaluate for yourself.
Safety-BeefySecure: Though the full position is always more complicated, the Safety Score is provided to simplify the key risk and safety considerations and kick-start your own due diligence. Our team carefully considers each factor before a vault is deployed, and keeps a watchful eye on each asset, chain and protocol which Beefy has integrated.

InfoCard-binSPIRIT-Work-Text: SpiritSwapâ€™s inSPIRIT governance token uses a vote locking model. binSPIRIT is a wrapped version of 4-year-locked inSPIRIT. inSPIRIT & binSPIRIT holders receive voting power, participation rewards, and boosted farming rewards. binSPIRIT holders can vote weekly on the gauges to receive SPIRIT emission allocation.
InfoCard-binSPIRIT-Bribes-Title: Use Beefyâ€™s Voting Power to Earn Bribes
InfoCard-binSPIRIT-Bribes-Text: 50% of Beefyâ€™s voting rights from locking SPIRIT are given to binSPIRIT holders. Beefy distributes these rights to binSPIRIT users to vote weekly via Snapshot. There is an open bribe environment for projects to bribe binSPIRIT holders for their voting power. Voters will receive bribes via an airdrop generated from the voting history.

pnl-graph-tooltip-deposit: Shows the current net deposit values denominated in both $USD and the deposit token(s). Subsequent deposits and withdrawals are added or subtracted respectively from the current total. For $USD values, deposits are valued at the current market price at the time of deposit and withdrawals are valued using a 'first in, first out' method.
pnl-graph-tooltip-now-vault: Shows the current net position values denominated in both $USD and the deposit token(s). The 'Now' captures price appreciation/depreciation as well as vault yield, and any trading-fee yield or liquid-staking yield.
pnl-graph-tooltip-now-clm: Shows the current net position values denominated in both $USD and the deposit token(s). The 'Now' captures price appreciation/depreciation as well as any trading-fee yield.
pnl-graph-tooltip-yield: Shows the current net yield generated by the vault, denominated in both $USD and the deposit token(s), as well as a percentage reflecting yield in tokens as a proportion of the 'At Deposit' net token quantity. The 'Yield' only reflects vault yield and does not capture trading-fee yield or any liquid-staking yield or boost yield.
pnl-graph-tooltip-pnl: Shows the current net profit or loss (PNL) of the position denominated in $USD, as well as a percentage reflecting PNL in $USD as a proportion of the 'At Deposit' net $USD value. The 'PNL' captures asset price appreciation/depreciation as well as vault yield, and any trading-fee yield or liquid-staking yield.
pnl-graph-tooltip-change-clm: Shows the current differences between the current position values and the deposit values, both denominated in the deposit tokens, as well as a PNL value reflecting the current net profit or loss (PNL) of the position denominated in $USD. The 'Hold' figure represents the current aggregate $USD value of the tokens deposited, to show the value the user would have had if the tokens were held rather than deposited.
pnl-graph-tooltip-change-clm-gov: Shows the difference between current position value and value at deposit, denominated in each deposit token. The PNL reflects the current net profit or loss in $USD, inclusive of all claimed and pending fees/rewards (including off-chain services like Merkl). Pending and claimed offchain rewards are valued at their current price; claimed onchain rewards using the price when claimed. The 'Hold' figure represents the current aggregate $USD value of the tokens deposited, to show the value the user would have had if the tokens were held rather than deposited.
pnl-graph-tooltip-autocompounded-fees-cl: Shows the current total of trading fees in each deposit token which have been earned, claimed and compounded into the user's position, denominated in both $USD and the deposit token.
pnl-graph-tooltip-pending-fees-clm: Shows the current total of trading fees in each deposit token which have been earned on the user's position but not yet claimed or compounded, denominated in both $USD and the deposit token.
pnl-graph-tooltip-total-fees-clm: Shows the current total of 'Pending Fees' and 'Autocompounding Fees' earned on the user's position, denominated in $USD.

PoolTogether-Content: PoolTogether is a prize savings protocol that gathers vault yield and randomly distributes it as prizes. Some PoolTogether prize vaults include bonus rewards on top of the yield, which funds prizes.
Details-Platform-Type-Description-amm: An 'Automated Market Maker' is a DeFi market or exchange that algorithmically and automatically allocates liquidity to fulfill traders' requests, by connecting different source sof liquidity and compensating those who provide it.
Details-Platform-Type-Description-alm: An 'Automated Liquidity Manager' is an applications which automate the process of providing and/or managing liquidity in DeFi.
Details-Platform-Type-Description-bridge: A 'Bridge Protocol' is a platform which facilitates the secure passage of assets and data between different blockchains by connecting different sources of liquidity and compensating those who provide it.
Details-Platform-Type-Description-money-: A 'Money Market' is a DeFi market or platform that algorithmically and automatically facilitates the lending and borrowing of assets and processes the payment and receipt of lending fees and interest.
Details-Platform-Type-Description-perps: A 'Perpetual Futures Exchange' is a DeFi market or platform that algorithmically and automatically facilitates the trading of derivative financial instruments to facilitate bidirectional exposure to asset pricing and process the payment and receipt of fees associated with using those instruments.
Details-Platform-Type-Description-yield-: A 'Yield Boost Protocol' is a DeFi platform that aims to boost the yields available through other DeFi protocols by aggregating voting power to direct incentives and efforts towards the products it builds on top of.
Details-Platform-Type-Description-farm: A 'Farming Protocol' is a DeFi system that enables users to earn rewards by providing liquidity or staking assets.
